The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: The salaried class might be spared from filing income-tax returns from next year provided there was no income from any other source. ?We are considering the proposal,? finance minister P. Chidambaram said. However, it depended on how soon the tax department put in place the fully online tax information network (TIN), he added.

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Growth in six infrastructure industries, which have a combined weight of 26.7 per cent in IIP, fell to 4.4 per cent during the first half of this fiscal from 5.3 per cent in the year-ago period. This was primarily because of a decline in the growth of crude petroleum, coal, electricity and cement. 

 Bhopal, Oct. 27: The Reserve Bank of India reviewed key economic, monetary and financial developments in the meeting of its central board of directors here today. The meeting, chaired by RBI governor Y.V. Reddy, was to provide an overall direction to the various affairs of the bank, sources said.

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Punjab National Bank has tied up with Metlife to offer group insurance to its customers. An account holder can pay Rs 228 a year for an insurance cover of Rs 1 lakh. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Maruti Udyog Ltd today launched a new version of its WagonR model priced at Rs 3.89 lakh (ex-showroom Delhi) with changes in the car?s interiors and exteriors.




